WEBVTT

00:01.666 --> 00:02.307
Well, happy new year.

00:06.192 --> 00:07.274
I hope you had a good Christmas.

00:08.035 --> 00:11.199
Nicola, the girl's night had a very relaxed Christmas.

00:13.482 --> 00:15.585
It was very calm, very peaceful.

00:16.266 --> 00:22.255
And so we feel really rested at the start of 2026, which is really nice, really nice.

00:22.755 --> 00:25.419
I can't quite get my head around the fact it's 2026 though.

00:25.539 --> 00:30.546
I was watching a little bit of the build up to the fireworks.

00:30.946 --> 00:32.228
on New Year's Day.

00:32.688 --> 00:37.854
We all sat down and we'd kind of watching, who was it, who was singing?

00:38.275 --> 00:38.836
What was his name?

00:39.777 --> 00:40.017
Pauline?

00:40.898 --> 00:44.202
Ronan Keaton, yeah, bit of Ronan Keaton, blast from the past.

00:44.422 --> 00:48.668
And we'd got there, we'd got there, we'd endured that part of the evening.

00:48.788 --> 00:56.437
And just as Big Ben was about to countdown, we needed to input a pinter sky that we couldn't actually remember.

00:56.517 --> 00:59.140
So we missed the whole of New Year fireworks.

00:59.701 --> 01:00.562
So, yeah.

01:00.706 --> 01:01.767
stayed up all that long.

01:03.009 --> 01:09.898
But during the kind of build-up to it, just as a throwaway comment, they said, it's 25 years since the millennium.

01:10.238 --> 01:15.125
We've had the first quarter of this century, and I was like, wow, that's amazing.

01:15.866 --> 01:28.242
Can anybody remember the millennium book that we all panicked about in the build-up to the millennium that we thought all computers, planes were going to drop out of the skies, and it was just going to be, yes, well, that didn't happen, did it, thankfully.

01:28.546 --> 01:37.154
Time flies by, time flies by, and at the start of every year, especially this year, I always feel a sense of optimism.

01:38.796 --> 01:43.280
Just as Lisa said, for me, it's the start of a new chapter.

01:43.320 --> 01:49.546
It's like turning the page of a new book, and excited to read the pages.

01:50.147 --> 01:57.714
In my perspective, I have, for the last three years, this will be my fourth year, I've had a journal that I've journaled in,

01:57.890 --> 02:04.657
maybe once or twice a week on average, just putting down some thoughts and reflections on what's going on in life.

02:04.777 --> 02:11.684
And I bought my new one on a New Year's Eve, and on New Year's Day I opened it up.

02:11.745 --> 02:17.410
And it's that new book, you know, the first page being written in, and all of these empty pages to be filled.

02:18.432 --> 02:21.835
And so I'm optimistic, I'm hopeful.

02:23.116 --> 02:24.658
I like fresh starts.

02:27.874 --> 02:31.179
But I know for some of you here, 2025 was really tough.

02:32.481 --> 02:44.060
You know, it's been a tough year and you look back and it's the start of 26 and maybe you're tired and it's just, you just think, oh man, it doesn't feel that optimistic because 2025 was difficult.

02:44.360 --> 02:47.625
It may be 2025 was really fantastic here.

02:47.665 --> 02:49.468
Lots of really great things happened.

02:50.149 --> 02:53.234
And you're looking at 2026 thinking, oh, we're more of the same.

02:53.602 --> 03:01.332
Or maybe for a lot of us, it might have been just one of those sort of average years, you know, nothing particularly special happened, nothing particularly difficult happened.

03:02.995 --> 03:08.442
But either whatever our story, 2026 is a new chapter.

03:09.844 --> 03:13.929
There is a sense of new start, new optimism.

03:15.331 --> 03:20.178
Yes, of course, 2026 is a sequel to 2025, which was a sequel to 2024.

03:21.359 --> 03:23.442
And just like,

03:23.554 --> 03:26.537
A book series, you open a new book and read the first page.

03:27.779 --> 03:30.201
It also builds on the pages that have come before.

03:31.342 --> 03:33.124
But it is a new start.

03:36.588 --> 03:37.489
It's my page two.

03:38.910 --> 03:41.133
I like to think of it as punctuation.

03:41.253 --> 03:44.597
I am not known for my grammar and punctuation.

03:45.217 --> 03:53.426
If there was marking for grammar and punctuation when I was at school, I would have got even worse grade in English.

03:53.826 --> 03:59.874
But I always think of like a new year, this moment in the year as a punctuation in our life.

04:01.175 --> 04:09.205
That breath that we take, and we think, right, what's actually important?

04:09.225 --> 04:10.407
What actually matters?

04:11.688 --> 04:13.410
What am I going to shoot for this year?

04:13.430 --> 04:15.533
What am I going to prioritize?

04:16.234 --> 04:19.238
It gives us space to stop and reflect.

04:20.099 --> 04:22.802
And in a way, that's what I want us to do this morning.

04:23.266 --> 04:31.759
is to stop and reflect and to think specifically about our faith and our journey with Jesus.

04:33.882 --> 04:45.981
In my last journal entry before the new year, I wrote a very sort of, this was my title, Order Out of the Chaos, was my title of my journal entry.

04:46.982 --> 04:52.210
And I think I was reflecting on, for six years really,

04:53.122 --> 04:54.784
Life has felt a little bit chaotic.

04:56.086 --> 05:00.593
We lived for a pandemic, I can't believe that one nearly six years since it started in March.

05:02.356 --> 05:05.280
And that was chaotic.

05:05.921 --> 05:14.393
Then family stuff with challenges has meant that life for us as a family has felt really quite chaotic.

05:14.433 --> 05:20.242
It's probably a strong word, but it's been really difficult to plan and to think ahead and to

05:20.738 --> 05:22.922
to kind of go, right, what are we gonna do this year?

05:22.982 --> 05:24.124
What are we gonna do this month?

05:24.284 --> 05:26.368
It's been one of those sorts of seasons.

05:28.211 --> 05:32.638
But I felt this year that the Lord was saying there's gonna be order out of the chaos.

05:34.261 --> 05:46.642
And I felt that the Lord said when I was writing it, that that is actually a prophetic word for some of us here today, but also for us as a church, that in the chaos of life, all of the things that have been really difficult and challenging.

05:47.586 --> 05:53.674
that this is gonna be year of order, that God is gonna bring a calmness to our lives.

05:55.497 --> 06:00.323
And that's not to say previous six years has been completely absent of planning and order.

06:00.644 --> 06:01.785
Of course that's not the case.

06:02.787 --> 06:09.176
But rather this year the winds are gonna quieten down and the rains are gonna cease a little.

06:10.497 --> 06:16.786
It's gonna be a calmer season, that's just what I felt as I was journaling for us as a family but actually for us as a church.

06:16.898 --> 06:19.201
and for many people here, individuals.

06:20.302 --> 06:22.285
And I was reminded of Genesis 1.

06:23.326 --> 06:25.930
It says this, in the beginning, God created the heavens and the earth.

06:26.370 --> 06:36.564
Now, the earth was formless and empty, darkness was over the surface of the deep, and the spirit of God was hovering over the waters, and God said, let there be light, and there was light.

06:38.146 --> 06:44.594
You know, I imagine, you know, I watch lots of sci-fi films, and you know, you go onto these barren sort of

06:44.994 --> 06:55.685
lands with no life and it's just sort of chaos and there's storms and there's wind and it's cold and and you just get this real sense of like this chaotic environment.

06:56.907 --> 07:14.866
And at the start of creation that's how I imagine the earth you know it's been created by God but it's formless and it's chaotic and then God just goes let there be light and suddenly there's light and then we know that over the next six periods of time he speaks

07:15.010 --> 07:16.151
creation into being.

07:16.812 --> 07:19.375
He speaks order into the chaos.

07:22.439 --> 07:34.094
So no matter what season we are in, whether that is a season that feels chaotic or where we're hanging on maybe even without... That would have been a good start, knocking things, flying.

07:35.055 --> 07:37.919
Whether we're hanging on with our fingernails.

07:39.401 --> 07:43.666
This is going to be a season, I believe, where there is going to be more calm and order.

07:45.154 --> 07:47.978
See, even in those chaotic times, God speaks.

07:49.741 --> 07:50.422
God speaks.

07:51.443 --> 07:53.607
From formlessness, is that even a word?

07:54.508 --> 07:58.574
And chaos, God speaks light, life and order into creation.

08:00.777 --> 08:04.483
And God speaks light, life and order into our lives too.

08:06.185 --> 08:08.609
He is with us in the difficult seasons.

08:09.470 --> 08:11.954
And when we build our life upon Jesus,

08:12.866 --> 08:19.873
He is always speaking life and order into our life, no matter what season we are in.

08:19.893 --> 08:24.799
I just think that is a word of knowledge for some of you today.

08:24.879 --> 08:33.027
And when we use a word of knowledge, we think of like a prophetic insight that God maybe gives us for certain individuals or maybe a group of people.

08:33.608 --> 08:36.951
And I just felt this was a prophetic word, an insight for people.

08:37.732 --> 08:39.474
Build your life on Jesus.

08:40.162 --> 08:43.906
and he will speak light, life and order in your future.

08:45.528 --> 08:53.416
You know, if you're here and you don't think your light is very full of light, it maybe feels a bit dark.

08:55.178 --> 09:05.810
If you feel like there is an absence of life, it feels really tricky and difficult and your life is a bit chaotic for various reasons.

09:07.554 --> 09:16.507
then really the key to today's talk is this, build your life on Jesus, because he's the one that brings light, life and order to our lives.

09:19.752 --> 09:25.320
Build your life on Jesus, that's really a word for us all at the start of 2024.

09:27.644 --> 09:34.514
So today we're starting a new series, that's just a lot of preamble, ramble, called Rooted.

09:35.458 --> 09:39.305
And at the center of this series is a very simple truth.

09:40.447 --> 09:43.633
Jesus is the only way truth and life.

09:44.755 --> 09:46.177
Nothing else is secure.

09:46.237 --> 09:49.142
Nothing else can satisfy.

09:50.445 --> 09:57.197
And we're gonna base the series or certainly kind of dip into this, into Psalm 1 as we go through the next five weeks.

09:58.158 --> 09:58.799
Let me read it to you.

09:58.880 --> 10:00.242
Blessed is the one.

10:00.322 --> 10:13.637
who does not walk in step with the wicked, or stand in the way that sinners take, or sit in the company of mockers, but whose delight is in the law of the Lord, and who meditates on his law day and night.

10:14.058 --> 10:23.068
That person is like a tree planted by streams of water, which yields its fruit and season, and whose leaf does not wither, whatever they do prospers.

10:23.829 --> 10:28.594
Not so the wicked, they are like chaff, that the wind blows away.

10:29.154 --> 10:33.959
Therefore, the wicked will not stand in the judgment nor sinners in the assembly of the righteous.

10:34.640 --> 10:41.226
For the Lord watches over the way of the righteous, but the way of the wicked leads to destruction.

10:42.768 --> 10:52.698
Psalm 1 creates this juxtaposition where we see the outcomes for a wicked life and a righteous life.

10:53.659 --> 10:57.042
And in verse 3, we have this wonderful picture.

10:58.818 --> 11:08.533
That person is like a tree planted by streams of water which yields its fruit in season and whose leaf does not wither whatever they do prosperous.

11:08.553 --> 11:11.738
And when I think of that passage, I think of something like this.

11:12.820 --> 11:16.306
So hopefully there should be a tree that appears on the screen.

11:17.207 --> 11:17.968
Something like that.

11:20.372 --> 11:26.802
A beautiful, vibrant tree planted next to a river that is just feeding it life.

11:28.930 --> 11:29.851
That's what I imagine.

11:30.652 --> 11:34.196
