12:26.498 --> 12:28.902
Ficus natalensis.

12:28.962 --> 12:33.749
I'm not looking at Darren Evans because he'll just laugh at me for trying to pronounce it.

12:34.810 --> 12:36.412
The roots go down 120 metres.

12:36.432 --> 12:39.176
Can you imagine that?

12:39.197 --> 12:40.238
120 metres.

12:40.538 --> 12:44.524
To ensure they have a flow of life giving water.

12:47.088 --> 12:50.653
A tree can be next to a river though and still die.

12:52.476 --> 12:53.938
If the roots are unhealthy,

12:54.242 --> 13:03.754
then no matter how much water and nutrients surround the tree, it will die or it will best survive, but without thriving and being fruitful.

13:05.196 --> 13:07.780
Someone tells us that we are like a tree.

13:09.262 --> 13:16.491
The question is, are we rooted in Jesus, the source of life, or have we placed our roots in other things?

13:17.913 --> 13:21.938
Are we embraced in the right of life or the wicked life?

13:24.322 --> 13:26.926
Here's a thought for you to just think about.

13:27.086 --> 13:34.076
A lot of plants, when drought stressed, will go to seed much more quickly.

13:35.338 --> 13:38.102
